		<div id="comment_body_64342991">I understand the technology just fine.  But the "social stigma" argument has nothing to do with technology at all.  It is universally used these days by people whose goods or services aren't as successful as the market leader, regardless of the industry.  It's a purely emotional attack vector that appeals to a certain segment of the political spectrum -- the segment that hates meritocracy and advocates victimhood.</div>
